{
  "stem": "14708.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Even before that.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Even before that, yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We went to a different dance school.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Naturally, teenagers went to dance school and dances.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But this was separate.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was one for the Christians, and one was for the Jews.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Big difference from the growing up in total assimilation in society.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Oh yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Oh yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yellow star.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "A very short while after that, I think beginning of May, they organized the ghetto in our city.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We lived in a part of the city where there were many Jews, so this part, this district, became the ghetto, which meant--",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We stayed, but in our three-room apartment, 54 people were crammed in.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Naturally, all our furniture, my piano, everything went out to the yard, and there were just mattresses put down.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in our kitchen, some 20 women tried to cook something.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were small children, babies-- it was hell, really.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was hell.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Very soon there was-- we heard that it is possible to go to work somewhere.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So I volunteered, and I went to work in a tobacco factory.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "This was done in such a way that every morning at 6 o'clock, we had to group in one place in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then a policeman came, and he took us out from the ghetto to the factory.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And in the evening, he took us back again.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, there were-- no, no.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was one policeman, one policeman.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I worked in this factory.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I must go back a little bit.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Just a month before the German occupation, on February 19, 1944, I first met my future husband, Jan.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He was teaching Hebrew the two brothers of my girlfriend, and she introduced us.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
